  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-09-06",
    "date": "2007-11-19T22:43:59Z",
    "text": "Camera Phone Predator Alert Act - Requires any mobile phone containing a digital camera to sound a tone whenever a photograph is taken with the camera's phone. Prohibits such a phone from being equipped with a means of disabling or silencing the tone. Treats the requirement as a consumer product safety standard and requires enforcement by the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC)."
  },
